<td>The primary version</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<h3>Do NOT Use Canonical Tags For</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Completely different pages.</strong> Canonicalizing unrelated content confuses Google. The tag gets ignored.</li>
<li><strong>Pagination.</strong> Do not point page 2, 3, and 4 back to page 1. Each paginated page has unique content. Use self-referencing canonicals on each page instead.</li>
<li><strong>Pages you want removed from the index.</strong> Use <code>noindex</code> for that. A canonical tag says "index this version." A <code>noindex</code> tag says "do not index at all." Using both on the same page sends contradictory signals.</li>
</ul>
<p>For redirect-specific guidance, see our <a href="/blog/301-redirects-guide/">301 redirects guide</a>.</p>
